[1] Zonguldak Province: wedding
Date: Sun 11 Jul 2021 07:58 TRT
Source: Aksam [in Turkish, trans., edited]
https://www.aksam.com.tr/yasam/dugun-yemegi-zehir-oldu-43-kisi-hastaneye-kaldirildi/haber-1187989


A total of 43 people who ate at a wedding in Zonguldak were treated at the hospital on suspicion of food poisoning. After a while, 43 people who ate at a wedding in the district reported complaints such as dizziness, nausea and vomiting. The sick were taken to various hospitals in the city.

It was learned that 43 people who were treated for food poisoning were in good health. It was reported that a sample of the food was taken while the investigation was started.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

******
[2] Gaziantep Province: swim meet
Date: Sun 11 Jul 2021 15:48 TRT
Source: NTV [in Turkish, trans., edited]
https://www.ntv.com.tr/yerel-haberler/gaziantep/gaziantepte-27-sporcu-gida-zehirlenmesi-suphesiyle-hastaneye-kaldirildi,IMygv3YxBkS_SNSasVok3Q


A total of 27 athletes aged 13-14 years who participated in the swimming championship in Gaziantep were hospitalized with the suspicion of food poisoning. The swimmers, who were in Gaziantep to participate in the Turkey Turkcell Long Course Junior Individual Swimming Championship, were treated for suspected food poisoning.

According to the information received, 27 athletes participating in the tournament organized in the city by the Turkish Swimming Federation were taken to various hospitals in the city on suspicion of food poisoning at night at the hotel where they stayed. According to the 1st determinations, it was learned that some of the athletes diagnosed with food poisoning were discharged, while the conditions of those who continued their treatment were good.

The tournament that started on Friday [9 Jul 2021] will end Sunday [11 Jul 2021].

--
Communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The incubation from the ingestion of the alleged food to the beginning of symptoms and the symptoms present (nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, presence or absence of fever) can be very useful in assessing the cause of the outbreaks.

The 2 provinces can be found on a map of the country at https://www.researchgate.net/figure/Map-of-Turkish-Provinces_fig1_299415818. Gaziantep is found in south-central Turkey and Zonguldak is in the north-central part of the country. - Mod.LL

